> 

@ryoppippi Nice! Thanks for the workaround. Can it be simplified as:

```lua
lspconfig.svelte.setup {
  on_attach = function(client)
    vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd("BufWritePost", {
      pattern = { "*.js", "*.ts" },
      callback = function(ctx)
        client.notify("$/onDidChangeTsOrJsFile", { uri = ctx.file })
      end,
    })
  end
}
```

@jasonlyu123 That makes sense. 

https://github.com/sveltejs/language-tools/blob/master/packages/language-server/src/server.ts#L110 Assume this is the code that checks and sets up fallback. 

Is there a better event we should be using?

@RichGuk @glepnir 
Thanks!
I tried this(https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/725#issuecomment-1539868397) without my autocmd configure, but it does not work for me
